-- Kategori: Career Tips
(1, '5 Tips Membangun Portfolio yang Menarik untuk Fresh Graduate', 
'Portfolio adalah salah satu aset paling penting dalam mencari pekerjaan, terutama bagi fresh graduate. Berikut adalah 5 tips untuk membangun portfolio yang menarik:\n\n1. **Tampilkan Project Terbaik Anda**\nPilih 3-5 project terbaik yang menunjukkan kemampuan Anda. Fokus pada kualitas, bukan kuantitas.\n\n2. **Ceritakan Proses di Balik Project**\nJelaskan problem yang Anda selesaikan, teknologi yang digunakan, dan hasil yang dicapai.\n\n3. **Buat Desain yang Clean dan Profesional**\nPortfolio yang rapi dan mudah dinavigasi akan meninggalkan kesan profesional.\n\n4. **Sertakan Link GitHub dan Demo**\nBerikan akses ke source code dan live demo agar recruiter bisa melihat langsung hasil karya Anda.\n\n5. **Update Secara Berkala**\nTambahkan project baru dan hapus project lama yang kurang relevan.\n\nDengan portfolio yang kuat, peluang Anda untuk dilirik perusahaan akan meningkat drastis!', 
'/images/articles/portfolio-tips.jpg', 
'Sarah Wijaya', 
'Career Tips', 
NOW(), NOW()),

(2, 'Cara Menulis CV yang ATS-Friendly agar Lolos Seleksi Awal', 
'Applicant Tracking System (ATS) adalah software yang digunakan perusahaan untuk menyaring CV secara otomatis. Agar CV Anda lolos:\n\n**1. Gunakan Format Sederhana**\nHindari desain yang terlalu rumit. Gunakan font standar seperti Arial, Calibri, atau Times New Roman.\n\n**2. Masukkan Keyword yang Relevan**\nBaca job description dengan teliti dan masukkan keyword penting ke dalam CV Anda.\n\n**3. Hindari Tabel dan Kolom**\nATS sering kesulitan membaca format tabel. Gunakan bullet points saja.\n\n**4. Simpan dalam Format .docx atau PDF**\nPastikan file Anda bisa dibaca oleh ATS. Format .docx biasanya paling aman.\n\n**5. Sertakan Section yang Jelas**\nGunakan heading standar seperti "Work Experience", "Education", "Skills".\n\n**6. Jangan Gunakan Header/Footer untuk Informasi Penting**\nATS sering tidak bisa membaca informasi di header/footer.\n\nDengan CV yang ATS-friendly, peluang Anda untuk sampai ke tahap interview akan jauh lebih besar!', 
'/images/articles/ats-cv.jpg', 
'Budi Santoso', 
'Career Tips', 
NOW(), NOW()),

(3, '10 Pertanyaan Interview Paling Sering Muncul dan Cara Menjawabnya', 
'Persiapan adalah kunci sukses dalam interview. Berikut 10 pertanyaan yang paling sering muncul:\n\n**1. "Ceritakan tentang diri Anda"**\nJawab dengan fokus pada pengalaman profesional, bukan personal life.\n\n**2. "Apa kelebihan dan kekurangan Anda?"**\nSebutkan kelebihan yang relevan dengan posisi. Untuk kekurangan, pilih yang tidak krusial dan jelaskan usaha perbaikan Anda.\n\n**3. "Kenapa Anda tertarik dengan posisi ini?"**\nTunjukkan riset Anda tentang perusahaan dan jelaskan bagaimana role ini sesuai dengan career goal Anda.\n\n**4. "Dimana Anda melihat diri Anda 5 tahun ke depan?"**\nTunjukkan ambisi yang realistis dan selaras dengan career path di perusahaan tersebut.\n\n**5. "Ceritakan pengalaman mengatasi konflik"**\nGunakan metode STAR (Situation, Task, Action, Result).\n\n**6. "Kenapa Anda resign dari pekerjaan sebelumnya?"**\nBerikan alasan positif, hindari berbicara buruk tentang perusahaan lama.\n\n**7. "Apa ekspektasi gaji Anda?"**\nLakukan riset market rate dan berikan range yang realistis.\n\n**8. "Bagaimana Anda bekerja dalam tim?"**\nBerikan contoh konkret dari pengalaman Anda.\n\n**9. "Apa yang membuat Anda unik?"**\nHighlight kombinasi skill dan pengalaman yang membedakan Anda.\n\n**10. "Apakah Anda punya pertanyaan untuk kami?"**\nSelalu siapkan 2-3 pertanyaan tentang perusahaan atau role yang menunjukkan antusiasme Anda.\n\nLatihan menjawab pertanyaan-pertanyaan ini akan membuat Anda lebih percaya diri saat interview!', 
'/images/articles/interview-questions.jpg', 
'Amanda Putri', 
'Career Tips', 
NOW(), NOW()),

(4, 'Strategi Networking yang Efektif untuk Meningkatkan Karir', 
'Networking bukan sekadar mengumpulkan kontak, tapi membangun relasi yang bermakna. Berikut strateginya:\n\n**1. Manfaatkan LinkedIn secara Maksimal**\n- Optimalkan profil LinkedIn Anda\n- Posting konten yang relevan dengan industri Anda\n- Engage dengan konten orang lain\n- Join grup profesional\n\n**2. Hadiri Event dan Seminar**\nEvent industri adalah tempat terbaik untuk bertemu profesional lain. Jangan hanya datang, tapi aktif bertanya dan berkenalan.\n\n**3. Follow Up Setelah Bertemu**\nKirim pesan terima kasih atau connect di LinkedIn dalam 24-48 jam setelah bertemu.\n\n**4. Berikan Value Lebih Dulu**\nNetworking bukan tentang "apa yang bisa saya dapat", tapi "apa yang bisa saya berikan". Share artikel, informasi, atau bantuan tanpa mengharapkan balasan.\n\n**5. Maintain Hubungan**\nJangan hanya menghubungi saat butuh sesuatu. Check-in secara berkala, ucapkan selamat atas achievement mereka.\n\n**6. Join Community**\nBergabung dengan komunitas profesional di bidang Anda, baik online maupun offline.\n\nNetworking yang kuat akan membuka banyak peluang karir yang tidak terlihat di job portal!', 
'/images/articles/networking.jpg', 
'Rudi Hartono', 
'Career Tips', 
NOW(), NOW()),

-- Kategori: Technology
(5, 'Roadmap Menjadi Full Stack Developer di 2025', 
'Full Stack Developer adalah salah satu profesi paling dicari di 2025. Berikut roadmap lengkapnya:\n\n**Phase 1: Foundation (2-3 bulan)**\n- HTML, CSS, JavaScript dasar\n- Git & GitHub\n- Command line basics\n- Responsive design\n\n**Phase 2: Frontend Development (3-4 bulan)**\n- React.js atau Vue.js\n- State management (Redux, Context API)\n- CSS frameworks (Tailwind, Bootstrap)\n- API integration\n\n**Phase 3: Backend Development (3-4 bulan)**\n- Node.js & Express.js atau Python & Django/Flask\n- Database SQL (PostgreSQL, MySQL)\n- Database NoSQL (MongoDB)\n- RESTful API design\n- Authentication & Authorization\n\n**Phase 4: DevOps Basics (2 bulan)**\n- Docker\n- CI/CD basics\n- Cloud deployment (AWS, Heroku, Vercel)\n\n**Phase 5: Advanced Topics (Ongoing)**\n- Testing (Jest, Cypress)\n- GraphQL\n- Microservices architecture\n- Performance optimization\n\n**Tips Sukses:**\n- Build real projects, bukan hanya tutorial\n- Contribute ke open source\n- Buat blog untuk document learning journey\n- Join developer community\n\nDengan konsistensi, dalam 12-18 bulan Anda bisa menjadi Full Stack Developer yang kompeten!', 
'/images/articles/fullstack-roadmap.jpg', 
'Andi Wijaya', 
'Technology', 
NOW(), NOW()),

(6, 'Mengenal AI dan Machine Learning untuk Pemula', 
'Artificial Intelligence (AI) dan Machine Learning (ML) adalah teknologi yang mengubah dunia. Mari kita pahami dasar-dasarnya:\n\n**Apa itu AI?**\nAI adalah kemampuan mesin untuk meniru kecerdasan manusia, seperti belajar, bernalar, dan memecahkan masalah.\n\n**Apa itu Machine Learning?**\nML adalah subset dari AI yang memungkinkan sistem belajar dari data tanpa perlu diprogram secara eksplisit.\n\n**Jenis-jenis Machine Learning:**\n\n1. **Supervised Learning**\nModel belajar dari data yang sudah dilabeli. Contoh: klasifikasi email spam/tidak spam.\n\n2. **Unsupervised Learning**\nModel menemukan pola dari data tanpa label. Contoh: customer segmentation.\n\n3. **Reinforcement Learning**\nModel belajar melalui trial and error dengan reward system. Contoh: game AI.\n\n**Tools untuk Memulai:**\n- Python (bahasa pemrograman utama)\n- Jupyter Notebook\n- Libraries: NumPy, Pandas, Scikit-learn\n- TensorFlow atau PyTorch untuk Deep Learning\n\n**Cara Memulai:**\n1. Pelajari Python basics\n2. Pahami statistik dan matematika dasar\n3. Ikuti course online (Coursera, edX)\n4. Praktek dengan dataset dari Kaggle\n5. Build project sederhana\n\nDengan dedikasi, siapa pun bisa belajar AI dan ML!', 
'/images/articles/ai-ml-intro.jpg', 
'Dr. Siti Nurhaliza', 
'Technology', 
NOW(), NOW()),

(7, 'Cloud Computing: AWS vs Azure vs Google Cloud - Mana yang Terbaik?', 
'Ketiga cloud provider ini mendominasi pasar. Mari kita bandingkan:\n\n**Amazon Web Services (AWS)**\n✅ Pros:\n- Market leader dengan layanan terlengkap\n- Dokumentasi sangat baik\n- Community support besar\n- Banyak job opportunities\n\n❌ Cons:\n- Pricing bisa kompleks\n- Learning curve cukup steep\n\n**Microsoft Azure**\n✅ Pros:\n- Integrasi sempurna dengan Microsoft products\n- Bagus untuk enterprise\n- Hybrid cloud solution terbaik\n- Strong in AI/ML services\n\n❌ Cons:\n- Interface kadang kurang intuitif\n- Dokumentasi tidak sekonsisten AWS\n\n**Google Cloud Platform (GCP)**\n✅ Pros:\n- Best in class untuk data analytics & ML\n- Pricing lebih transparan\n- Performance excellent\n- Kubernetes native (invented by Google)\n\n❌ Cons:\n- Market share lebih kecil\n- Fewer job opportunities\n- Layanan enterprise kurang mature\n\n**Rekomendasi:**\n- **Untuk pemula:** GCP (pricing jelas, UI clean)\n- **Untuk job market:** AWS (paling banyak dicari)\n- **Untuk enterprise/corporate:** Azure\n- **Untuk data science/ML:** GCP atau AWS\n\nPilih yang sesuai dengan career goal dan industri yang Anda targetkan!', 
'/images/articles/cloud-comparison.jpg', 
'Michael Tan', 
'Technology', 
NOW(), NOW()),

(8, 'Panduan Lengkap Cyber Security untuk Developer', 
'Security adalah tanggung jawab setiap developer. Berikut panduan dasarnya:\n\n**1. Authentication & Authorization**\n- Gunakan password hashing (bcrypt, argon2)\n- Implement JWT dengan proper expiration\n- Multi-factor authentication untuk sensitive operations\n- Never store passwords in plain text\n\n**2. Input Validation**\n- Validasi semua input dari user\n- Sanitize data untuk prevent XSS\n- Use parameterized queries untuk prevent SQL injection\n- Implement rate limiting\n\n**3. Data Protection**\n- Encrypt sensitive data at rest\n- Use HTTPS untuk semua connections\n- Implement CORS dengan proper configuration\n- Never expose API keys di frontend code\n\n**4. Dependency Management**\n- Regularly update dependencies\n- Use tools seperti npm audit atau Snyk\n- Review third-party libraries sebelum digunakan\n\n**5. Error Handling**\n- Jangan expose sensitive information di error messages\n- Log errors securely\n- Implement proper error boundaries\n\n**6. Security Testing**\n- Penetration testing\n- Code review dengan focus on security\n- Use OWASP Top 10 sebagai checklist\n\n**Tools yang Berguna:**\n- OWASP ZAP\n- Burp Suite\n- SonarQube\n- Snyk\n\n**Best Practices:**\n- Principle of least privilege\n- Defense in depth\n- Security by design, not afterthought\n\nSecurity bukan feature, tapi requirement!', 
'/images/articles/cybersecurity.jpg', 
'Farhan Maulana', 
'Technology', 
NOW(), NOW()),

-- Kategori: Personal Development
(9, 'Time Management untuk Profesional yang Sibuk', 
'Mengelola waktu dengan baik adalah skill paling penting untuk produktivitas. Berikut tekniknya:\n\n**1. Pomodoro Technique**\n- Kerja fokus 25 menit\n- Break 5 menit\n- Setelah 4 pomodoro, break 15-30 menit\n\n**2. Time Blocking**\n- Block waktu di calendar untuk specific tasks\n- Treat appointments dengan diri sendiri seperti meetings\n- Include buffer time antar tasks\n\n**3. Eat the Frog**\n- Kerjakan task paling berat di pagi hari\n- Energy paling tinggi untuk task paling challenging\n\n**4. Two-Minute Rule**\n- Jika task bisa selesai dalam 2 menit, kerjakan sekarang\n- Hindari accumulation of small tasks\n\n**5. Weekly Review**\n- Review progress setiap minggu\n- Plan week ahead\n- Adjust priorities\n\n**Tools yang Membantu:**\n- Todoist atau TickTick untuk task management\n- Google Calendar untuk time blocking\n- Forest atau Freedom untuk focus\n- RescueTime untuk time tracking\n\n**Tips Bonus:**\n- Learn to say NO\n- Delegate when possible\n- Batch similar tasks together\n- Minimize context switching\n\nDengan time management yang baik, Anda bisa achieve more dengan stress less!', 
'/images/articles/time-management.jpg', 
'Linda Kusuma', 
'Personal Development', 
NOW(), NOW()),

(10, 'Growth Mindset: Kunci Sukses di Era Digital', 
'Growth mindset adalah belief bahwa kemampuan bisa dikembangkan melalui dedikasi dan kerja keras.\n\n**Fixed Mindset vs Growth Mindset:**\n\n**Fixed Mindset mengatakan:**\n- "Saya tidak berbakat"\n- "Ini terlalu sulit untuk saya"\n- "Saya gagal"\n\n**Growth Mindset mengatakan:**\n- "Saya bisa belajar ini"\n- "Ini challenging, tapi saya akan coba"\n- "Saya belajar dari kegagalan"\n\n**Cara Mengembangkan Growth Mindset:**\n\n1. **Embrace Challenges**\nLihat tantangan sebagai opportunity to grow, bukan ancaman.\n\n2. **Learn from Criticism**\nFeedback adalah gift untuk improvement, bukan personal attack.\n\n3. **Celebrate Process, Not Just Results**\nApresiasi effort dan progress, bukan hanya achievement.\n\n4. **View Failure as Learning**\nSetiap failure adalah data untuk improvement.\n\n5. **Be Inspired by Others Success**\nJadikan success orang lain sebagai motivasi, bukan jealousy.\n\n**Praktik Harian:**\n- Replace "I can\'t" dengan "I can\'t yet"\n- Journal tentang what you learned hari ini\n- Set learning goals, bukan hanya performance goals\n- Surround yourself dengan growth-minded people\n\n**Impact dalam Karir:**\n- Lebih mudah adapt dengan perubahan\n- Continuous learning dan upskilling\n- Resilient menghadapi setbacks\n- Innovation dan creativity meningkat\n\nGrowth mindset adalah superpower di era yang constantly changing ini!', 
'/images/articles/growth-mindset.jpg', 
'Dewi Lestari', 
'Personal Development', 
NOW(), NOW()),

(11, 'Work-Life Balance di Era Remote Working', 
'Remote working memberikan flexibility, tapi juga challenges untuk work-life balance.\n\n**Challenges Remote Working:**\n- Sulit separate work dan personal time\n- Always-on culture\n- Isolation dan loneliness\n- Distractions di rumah\n\n**Strategi untuk Balance:**\n\n**1. Set Clear Boundaries**\n- Tentukan jam kerja yang jelas\n- Communicate availability ke team\n- Turn off notifications di luar jam kerja\n\n**2. Create Dedicated Workspace**\n- Pisahkan area kerja dengan area personal\n- Invest in ergonomic setup\n- Ketika kerja selesai, tinggalkan workspace\n\n**3. Maintain Routine**\n- Wake up dan sleep di waktu yang sama\n- Morning routine sebelum mulai kerja\n- Evening routine untuk wind down\n\n**4. Take Breaks**\n- Stand dan stretch setiap jam\n- Lunch break tanpa laptop\n- Short walk untuk fresh air\n\n**5. Stay Connected**\n- Virtual coffee dengan colleagues\n- Join co-working space sesekali\n- Attend community events\n\n**6. Prioritize Health**\n- Exercise regularly\n- Eat healthy meals\n- Get enough sleep\n- Mental health check-ins\n\n**Red Flags of Burnout:**\n- Constantly tired\n- Decreased productivity\n- Cynicism about work\n- Physical symptoms (headaches, insomnia)\n\nJika mengalami burnout, take time off dan seek support. Remember, you can\'t pour from an empty cup!', 
'/images/articles/work-life-balance.jpg', 
'Rina Susanti', 
'Personal Development', 
NOW(), NOW()),

-- Kategori: Industry Insights
(12, 'Tren Teknologi 2025 yang Akan Mengubah Industri', 
'Teknologi berkembang dengan cepat. Berikut tren yang akan mendominasi 2025:\n\n**1. Generative AI Goes Mainstream**\n- AI co-pilots dalam berbagai profesi\n- Automated content creation\n- Personalized AI assistants\n- Impact: Perubahan cara kerja di hampir semua industri\n\n**2. Quantum Computing Breakthroughs**\n- Solving complex problems di pharmaceutical, finance\n- Cryptography revolution\n- Impact: Breakthrough dalam drug discovery, optimization problems\n\n**3. Edge Computing Expansion**\n- Processing data closer to source\n- Reduced latency untuk IoT devices\n- Impact: Real-time applications, autonomous vehicles\n\n**4. Sustainable Tech**\n- Green cloud computing\n- Carbon-neutral data centers\n- Circular economy dalam tech hardware\n- Impact: Pressure pada companies untuk reduce carbon footprint\n\n**5. Web3 Evolution**\n- Decentralized applications\n- NFTs beyond art (credentials, tickets)\n- Impact: New business models, digital ownership\n\n**6. 5G & 6G Development**\n- Ultra-fast connectivity\n- Enable new use cases (remote surgery, holographic calls)\n- Impact: Infrastructure for next-gen applications\n\n**7. Cybersecurity Mesh**\n- Distributed security approach\n- Zero-trust architecture\n- Impact: Better protection against sophisticated attacks\n\n**Skills to Develop:**\n- AI/ML proficiency\n- Cloud-native development\n- Cybersecurity fundamentals\n- Sustainability awareness\n\nStay ahead dengan continuous learning!', 
'/images/articles/tech-trends-2025.jpg', 
'Prof. Ahmad Yani', 
'Industry Insights', 
NOW(), NOW()),

(13, 'Startup vs Corporate: Mana yang Cocok untuk Karir Anda?', 
'Pilihan antara startup dan corporate sangat personal. Mari kita analisis:\n\n**STARTUP**\n\n**✅ Pros:**\n- Rapid learning curve\n- Wear multiple hats (generalist skills)\n- Direct impact on company growth\n- Equity/stock options potential\n- Flat hierarchy, easy access to founders\n- Fast decision making\n- Innovative environment\n\n**❌ Cons:**\n- Job security lower\n- Work-life balance challenging\n- Limited resources\n- Salary kadang di bawah market rate\n- Benefits terbatas\n- High pressure\n\n**Cocok untuk Anda jika:**\n- Early career, ingin learn fast\n- Risk taker\n- Passionate tentang mission startup\n- Ingin rapid career growth\n\n**CORPORATE**\n\n**✅ Pros:**\n- Job stability\n- Structured career path\n- Comprehensive benefits\n- Training & development programs\n- Work-life balance lebih baik\n- Brand name untuk CV\n- Resources melimpah\n\n**❌ Cons:**\n- Slower career progression\n- Bureaucracy\n- Less autonomy\n- Specialized roles (less variety)\n- Impact individual less visible\n- Slow decision making\n\n**Cocok untuk Anda jika:**\n- Value stability\n- Want structured career path\n- Life priorities (family, dll)\n- Prefer specialized expertise\n\n**Hybrid Path:**\nBanyak professionals start di corporate untuk build foundation, lalu move ke startup, atau sebaliknya.\n\n**Bottom Line:**\nNo right or wrong choice. Pilih based on:\n- Current life stage\n- Risk tolerance\n- Learning goals\n- Financial needs\n- Personal values\n\nYou can always switch later!', 
'/images/articles/startup-vs-corporate.jpg', 
'Yoga Pratama', 
'Industry Insights', 
NOW(), NOW()),

(14, 'Gaji Developer di Indonesia: Panduan Lengkap 2025', 
'Mari kita bahas salary range untuk berbagai level developer di Indonesia:\n\n**JUNIOR DEVELOPER (0-2 years)**\n- Startup: Rp 5-8 juta/bulan\n- Corporate: Rp 7-12 juta/bulan\n- Remote foreign company: $800-1,500/bulan\n\n**MID-LEVEL DEVELOPER (2-5 years)**\n- Startup: Rp 8-15 juta/bulan\n- Corporate: Rp 12-20 juta/bulan\n- Remote foreign company: $1,500-3,000/bulan\n\n**SENIOR DEVELOPER (5+ years)**\n- Startup: Rp 15-25 juta/bulan\n- Corporate: Rp 20-35 juta/bulan\n- Remote foreign company: $3,000-6,000/bulan\n\n**TECH LEAD / ARCHITECT**\n- Rp 25-45 juta/bulan\n- Remote foreign: $5,000-8,000/bulan\n\n**ENGINEERING MANAGER**\n- Rp 30-60 juta/bulan\n- Remote foreign: $6,000-10,000/bulan\n\n**SKILLS YANG BOOST SALARY:**\n- Cloud (AWS, Azure, GCP)\n- DevOps & Kubernetes\n- System Design\n- AI/ML\n- Blockchain\n- Mobile (React Native, Flutter)\n\n**TIPS NEGOTIATION:**\n1. Research market rate (Glassdoor, levels.fyi)\n2. Know your value (skills, experience, impact)\n3. Consider total compensation (salary + benefits + equity)\n4. Be ready to walk away\n5. Get competing offers untuk leverage\n\n**BEYOND SALARY:**\n- Learning opportunities\n- Career growth\n- Work culture\n- Team quality\n- Product/mission\n\nRemember, highest salary doesn\'t always mean best career move. Consider long-term growth!', 
'/images/articles/developer-salary.jpg', 
'Indra Gunawan', 
'Industry Insights', 
NOW(), NOW()),

-- Kategori: Learning Tips
(15, 'Cara Belajar Programming secara Efektif untuk Pemula', 
'Belajar programming bisa overwhelming. Berikut panduan efektifnya:\n\n**1. Pilih Satu Bahasa, Master Dulu**\nJangan language hopping. Pilih satu (Python untuk beginners recommended), kuasai fundamentals.\n\n**2. Learn by Doing, Not Just Watching**\n- Setiap tutorial, code along\n- Modify code, experiment\n- Break things dan fix them\n\n**3. Build Projects**\nJangan stuck di tutorial hell. After basics, langsung build:\n- Start simple (calculator, to-do list)\n- Gradually increase complexity\n- Build what interests you\n\n**4. Read Other People\'s Code**\n- Explore GitHub repositories\n- Understand different coding styles\n- Learn best practices\n\n**5. Debug Like a Pro**\n- Don\'t just copy-paste solutions\n- Understand WHY error terjadi\n- Use debugger tools\n\n**6. Learn to Google**\n- Phrasing questions correctly\n- Read documentation\n- Stack Overflow dengan bijak\n\n**7. Join Community**\n- Discord, Slack groups\n- Local meetups\n- Help others (teaching reinforces learning)\n\n**8. Consistent Practice**\n- Code everyday, even 30 minutes\n- Consistency beats intensity\n\n**Common Pitfalls to Avoid:**\n- Tutorial hell (watching tanpa practice)\n- Perfectionism (waiting until "ready")\n- Comparing dengan yang sudah advanced\n- Giving up when stuck\n\n**Learning Resources:**\n- FreeCodeCamp\n- The Odin Project\n- CS50 (Harvard)\n- Documentation official\n\n**Mindset:**\n- Everyone started as beginner\n- Confusion is part of learning process\n- Every expert was once a beginner\n\nRemember: Progress > Perfection. Keep coding!', 
'/images/articles/learn-programming.jpg', 
'Rizki Firmansyah', 
'Learning Tips', 
NOW(), NOW()),

(16, 'Menguasai Data Structures & Algorithms untuk Interview', 
'DSA adalah kunci untuk crack technical interviews. Berikut roadmap lengkapnya:\n\n**Phase 1: Fundamentals**\n\n**Arrays & Strings**\n- Two pointers technique\n- Sliding window\n- Common operations\n\n**Linked Lists**\n- Single, double, circular\n- Fast & slow pointers\n- Reversal\n\n**Stacks & Queues**\n- LIFO vs FIFO\n- Implementation\n- Common use cases\n\n**Phase 2: Non-Linear Structures**\n\n**Trees**\n- Binary trees\n- Binary search trees\n- Tree traversals (inorder, preorder, postorder)\n- Level order traversal\n\n**Graphs**\n- Representation (adjacency list/matrix)\n- DFS dan BFS\n- Shortest path algorithms\n\n**Heaps**\n- Min heap & max heap\n- Priority queue\n- Heap operations\n\n**Phase 3: Algorithms**\n\n**Sorting**\n- Quick sort, merge sort\n- Time & space complexity\n\n**Searching**\n- Binary search\n- Variations\n\n**Dynamic Programming**\n- Memoization\n- Tabulation\n- Common patterns\n\n**Greedy Algorithms**\n- When to use\n- Common problems\n\n**Phase 4: Advanced**\n- Tries\n- Union Find\n- Segment Trees\n- Bit Manipulation\n\n**Practice Strategy:**\n\n1. **Understand, Don\'t Memorize**\n   - Why algorithm works\n   - Trade-offs\n\n2. **Pattern Recognition**\n   - Group similar problems\n   - Identify which technique to use\n\n3. **Solve by Difficulty**\n   - Start with Easy\n   - Move to Medium after comfortable\n   - Hard untuk advanced preparation\n\n4. **Time Yourself**\n   - Simulate interview conditions\n   - 20-30 minutes per problem\n\n5. **Review Solutions**\n   - Multiple approaches\n   - Optimize\n\n**Resources:**\n- LeetCode (best for interview prep)\n- HackerRank\n- AlgoExpert\n- Cracking the Coding Interview book\n\n**Timeline:**\n- Dedicate 2-3 hours daily\n- 2-3 months untuk solid preparation\n\n**During Interview:**\n- Think out loud\n- Ask clarifying questions\n- Start with brute force, then optimize\n- Test dengan edge cases\n\nConsistency is key. Happy coding!', 
'/images/articles/dsa-interview.jpg', 
'Kevin Susanto', 
'Learning Tips', 
NOW(), NOW()),

(17, 'Belajar Bahasa Inggris untuk Profesional IT', 
'English proficiency adalah game-changer untuk IT career. Berikut cara efektif belajarnya:\n\n**Why English Matters:**\n- Documentation mostly in English\n- Remote job opportunities\n- Global collaboration\n- Higher salary potential\n- Access to latest tech resources\n\n**Skills to Focus:**\n\n**1. Reading (Highest Priority)**\n- Tech documentation\n- Articles & blogs\n- Code comments\n\n**Practice:**\n- Read Medium articles daily\n- Follow dev.to\n- Read official documentation\n\n**2. Writing**\n- Documentation\n- Code comments\n- Emails & Slack messages\n- Technical blogs\n\n**Practice:**\n- Comment your code in English\n- Write technical blog\n- Participate di forums (Stack Overflow, Reddit)\n\n**3. Listening**\n- Tech talks & conferences\n- Podcasts\n- Video tutorials\n\n**Practice:**\n- Watch YouTube tech channels\n- Listen to podcasts (Syntax.fm, JavaScript Jabber)\n- Watch conference talks\n\n**4. Speaking**\n- Meetings\n- Presentations\n- Interviews\n\n**Practice:**\n- Record yourself explaining code\n- Join English speaking communities\n- Practice mock interviews\n\n**Technical Vocabulary:**\n\n**Common Terms:**\n- Deploy, debug, refactor\n- Scalability, reliability, maintainability\n- API endpoint, payload, response\n- Repository, commit, merge\n\n**Phrases:**\n- "Let me walk you through..."\n- "The main challenge here is..."\n- "We can approach this by..."\n- "The trade-off is..."\n\n**Learning Strategy:**\n\n1. **Immersion**\n   - Change phone/computer language to English\n   - Join English tech communities\n\n2. **Daily Practice**\n   - 30 minutes reading\n   - 15 minutes listening\n   - Write 1 paragraph about what you learned\n\n3. **Active Usage**\n   - Think in English\n   - Talk to yourself about code\n\n4. **Spaced Repetition**\n   - Use Anki for technical vocabulary\n\n**Resources:**\n- Grammarly (untuk writing)\n- HelloTalk (practice dengan native speakers)\n- Coursera (technical courses in English)\n- Podcasts untuk commute time\n\n**Mindset:**\n- Don\'t aim for perfect, aim for clear communication\n- Mistakes are learning opportunities\n- Focus on technical English first, general English akan follow\n\nDalam 6-12 bulan consistent practice, English won\'t be barrier anymore!', 
'/images/articles/english-for-it.jpg', 
'Diana Safitri', 
'Learning Tips', 
NOW(), NOW()),

-- Kategori: Freelancing
(18, 'Memulai Karir sebagai Freelance Developer: Panduan Lengkap', 
'Freelancing menawarkan freedom dan flexibility. Berikut cara memulainya:\n\n**PERSIAPAN**\n\n**1. Build Strong Portfolio**\n- 3-5 quality projects\n- Diverse skills showcase\n- Live demos\n- Clear case studies\n\n**2. Define Your Niche**\nJangan jadi jack of all trades. Specialize:\n- Frontend React/Vue\n- Backend Node/Python\n- Mobile React Native/Flutter\n- Full Stack\n\nSpecialization = higher rates.\n\n**3. Set Up Professional Presence**\n- Website/portfolio\n- LinkedIn optimization\n- GitHub dengan good repositories\n- Professional email\n\n**FINDING CLIENTS**\n\n**Platforms:**\n- Upwork (largest marketplace)\n- Toptal (high-paying, selective)\n- Projects.co.id (Indonesia)\n- LinkedIn (direct outreach)\n\n**Cold Outreach:**\n- Identify target clients\n- Personalized emails\n- Offer value upfront\n- Follow up\n\n**Networking:**\n- Local tech meetups\n- Online communities\n- Referrals from past clients\n\n**PRICING STRATEGY**\n\n**Hourly vs Fixed Price:**\n- Hourly: good untuk unclear scope\n- Fixed: better untuk well-defined projects\n\n**Rate Guidelines (Indonesia):**\n- Junior: Rp 75-150k/jam\n- Mid: Rp 150-300k/jam\n- Senior: Rp 300-600k/jam\n\n**Value-Based Pricing:**\nPrice based on value delivered, bukan time spent.\n\n**CLIENT MANAGEMENT**\n\n**1. Clear Communication**\n- Set expectations upfront\n- Regular updates\n- Document everything\n\n**2. Contracts**\n- Always use contract\n- Define scope, timeline, payment terms\n- Include revision limits\n\n**3. Payment Terms**\n- 50% upfront, 50% on completion (small projects)\n- Milestone-based (large projects)\n- Use escrow for security\n\n**4. Over-Deliver**\n- Meet deadlines\n- Exceed expectations\n- Great clients come from referrals\n\n**COMMON CHALLENGES**\n\n**Scope Creep:**\n- Define scope clearly\n- Charge for additional requests\n\n**Late Payments:**\n- Payment terms in contract\n- Stop work jika payment overdue\n\n**Difficult Clients:**\n- Red flags: unclear requirements, price haggling, disrespectful\n- Learn to say NO\n\n**Feast or Famine:**\n- Always be marketing\n- Build pipeline\n- Save for slow months\n\n**TOOLS**\n- Time tracking: Toggl\n- Invoicing: Wave, PayPal\n- Project management: Trello, Asana\n- Communication: Slack, Zoom\n\n**TAXES & LEGALITY**\n- Register sebagai freelancer\n- Track income & expenses\n- Set aside untuk pajak\n- Consider forming PT untuk scale\n\n**SUCCESS TIPS**\n- Start part-time sebelum full-time\n- Build emergency fund (6 months)\n- Continuous learning\n- Treat it like business, not side gig\n\nFreelancing bukan easy path, tapi very rewarding untuk yang disciplined!', 
'/images/articles/freelance-developer.jpg', 
'Hendra Wijaya', 
'Freelancing', 
NOW(), NOW()),

(19, 'Platform Freelance Terbaik untuk Developer Indonesia', 
'Memilih platform freelance yang tepat sangat penting. Berikut analisis lengkapnya:\n\n**1. UPWORK**\n\n**Rating: 4/5**\n\n**Pros:**\n- Largest client base\n- International exposure\n- Built-in payment protection\n- Various project types\n\n**Cons:**\n- High competition\n- 20% commission (turun seiring earnings)\n- Hard untuk beginners (need connects)\n\n**Tips:**\n- Specialized niche profile\n- Take tests untuk credibility\n- Start dengan lower rates untuk build reviews\n\n**Best For:**\nDevelopers dengan portfolio solid, siap compete globally.\n\n**2. TOPTAL**\n\n**Rating: 5/5 (if you get in)**\n\n**Pros:**\n- Top 3% developers only\n- Very high rates ($60-200/hour)\n- Quality clients\n- Minimal administrative hassle\n\n**Cons:**\n- Extremely selective (screening process ketat)\n- Need strong experience\n\n**Best For:**\nSenior developers dengan proven track record.\n\n**3. FIVERR**\n\n**Rating: 3/5**\n\n**Pros:**\n- Easy to start\n- Clients come to you\n- Good untuk package services\n\n**Cons:**\n- Race to bottom pricing\n- 20% commission\n- Hard to charge premium rates\n\n**Tips:**\n- Create specific gigs\n- Showcase portfolio\n- Over-deliver untuk good reviews\n\n**Best For:**\nBeginners, atau specific services (e.g., "WordPress bug fix").\n\n**4. FREELANCER.COM**\n\n**Rating: 2.5/5**\n\n**Pros:**\n- Many projects\n- Contest opportunities\n\n**Cons:**\n- Extreme low-balling\n- Quality clients rare\n- Complicated fee structure\n\n**Best For:**\nNot recommended unless very beginning.\n\n**5. PROJECTS.CO.ID**\n\n**Rating: 3.5/5**\n\n**Pros:**\n- Indonesian market\n- Local payment methods\n- Less competition from global developers\n\n**Cons:**\n- Lower rates compared to international\n- Smaller project volume\n\n**Best For:**\nDevelopers preferring Indonesian clients, payment di rupiah.\n\n**6. SRIBULANCER**\n\n**Rating: 3/5**\n\n**Pros:**\n- Local Indonesian platform\n- Rupiah transactions\n- Understand local market\n\n**Cons:**\n- Limited high-value projects\n- Small client base\n\n**Best For:**\nEntry-level freelancers di Indonesia.\n\n**7. LINKEDIN (Direct Outreach)**\n\n**Rating: 4.5/5**\n\n**Pros:**\n- No commission\n- Build long-term relationships\n- Professional networking\n\n**Cons:**\n- Requires active effort\n- Slower to start\n\n**Tips:**\n- Optimize profile\n- Share valuable content\n- Engage dengan potential clients\n- Direct message dengan value proposition\n\n**Best For:**\nAll levels, especially yang mau build sustainable business.\n\n**RECOMMENDATION BY LEVEL:**\n\n**Beginner:**\n1. Fiverr (easy start)\n2. Projects.co.id (local)\n3. Upwork (build experience)\n\n**Intermediate:**\n1. Upwork (main income)\n2. LinkedIn (direct clients)\n3. Projects.co.id (additional)\n\n**Advanced:**\n1. Toptal (if qualified)\n2. LinkedIn (primary)\n3. Direct clients from network\n\n**PRO TIPS:**\n\n1. **Multi-Platform Strategy**\nJangan depend on satu platform. Diversify.\n\n2. **Move Off-Platform**\nOnce trust built, move clients off-platform untuk avoid fees.\n\n3. **Build Personal Brand**\nLong-term, clients should come to you directly.\n\n4. **International vs Local**\nInternational rates higher, tapi competition tougher. Balance both.\n\nRemember: Platform adalah starting point. Goal akhir adalah sustainable business dengan repeat clients!', 
'/images/articles/freelance-platforms.jpg', 
'Siska Amelia', 
'Freelancing', 
NOW(), NOW()),

(20, 'Mengelola Keuangan sebagai Freelancer', 
'Financial management adalah crucial skill untuk freelancer. Berikut panduannya:\n\n**INCOME MANAGEMENT**\n\n**1. Variable Income Reality**\nFreelance income tidak stabil. Some months ramai, some sepi.\n\n**Solution:**\n- Calculate average monthly income (6-12 months)\n- Budget based on lowest month\n- Save surplus dari good months\n\n**2. Emergency Fund**\n**Target: 6-12 months expenses**\n\nBuild gradually:\n- Month 1-3: 1 month expenses\n- Month 4-6: 3 months expenses\n- Month 7-12: 6 months expenses\n\n**3. Payment Terms**\n\n**Standard Terms:**\n- 50% upfront, 50% on delivery (small projects)\n- Milestone-based (large projects)\n- NET 15 or NET 30 untuk corporate clients\n\n**Late Payment Strategy:**\n- Clear terms in contract\n- Send reminder H-3 before due\n- Follow up on due date\n- Stop work jika severely overdue\n- Late payment fees (if in contract)\n\n**EXPENSE TRACKING**\n\n**Essential Expenses:**\n- Internet (crucial)\n- Laptop & maintenance\n- Software subscriptions\n- Co-working space (optional)\n- Learning & courses\n- Accounting/legal\n\n**Tools:**\n- Expense tracking: Wallet by BudgetBakers\n- Invoicing: Wave, PayPal\n- Spreadsheet untuk manual tracking\n\n**TAX PLANNING**\n\n**Tax Obligations:**\n- PPh (Pajak Penghasilan)\n- Report income annually\n\n**Deductible Expenses:**\n- Equipment & software\n- Internet & phone\n- Office space\n- Professional development\n- Transportation untuk client meetings\n\n**Tips:**\n- Set aside 20-30% untuk pajak\n- Separate account untuk pajak\n- Consult dengan tax professional\n- Keep all receipts\n\n**PRICING STRATEGY**\n\n**Calculate Your Hourly Rate:**\n\n```\nYearly income target: Rp 200,000,000\nBillable hours: 1,000 hours/year (20 hours/week)\nBase rate: Rp 200,000/hour\n\nAdd 30% overhead (tax, expenses, downtime)\nFinal rate: Rp 260,000/hour\n```\n\n**Don\'t Forget:**\n- Not all time is billable\n- Account for sick days, vacation\n- Marketing & admin time\n\n**INVESTMENT & RETIREMENT**\n\n**No employer benefits = self-funded retirement**\n\n**Options:**\n- Reksadana (mutual funds)\n- Stocks (for long-term)\n- Property (jika sudah stable income)\n- BPJS Ketenagakerjaan (government program)\n\n**Allocation:**\n- 50% living expenses\n- 30% savings & emergency fund\n- 20% investments & retirement\n\n**INSURANCE**\n\n**Must-Have:**\n- Health insurance (BPJS + private)\n- Laptop/equipment insurance\n\n**Consider:**\n- Life insurance (jika ada dependents)\n- Disability insurance\n\n**SCALING INCOME**\n\n**Strategies:**\n\n1. **Increase Rates**\n   - Review annually\n   - Charge more untuk new clients\n   - Value-based pricing\n\n2. **Productize Services**\n   - Package services\n   - Fixed scope & price\n   - Scalable delivery\n\n3. **Passive Income**\n   - Create courses\n   - Write ebooks\n   - Build SaaS products\n\n4. **Hire/Subcontract**\n   - Delegate tasks\n   - Take bigger projects\n   - White-label services\n\n**COMMON FINANCIAL MISTAKES**\n\n❌ **Lifestyle Inflation**\nJangan naikkan expenses seiring income naik.\n\n❌ **No Separation**\nMix personal & business finances.\n\n**Solution:** Separate bank accounts.\n\n❌ **Underpricing**\nRace to bottom untuk get clients.\n\n**Solution:** Know your value, charge accordingly.\n\n❌ **No Retirement Planning**\nFocus on present, forget future.\n\n**Solution:** Start small, invest regularly.\n\n**FINANCIAL GOALS**\n\n**Short-term (1 year):**\n- Emergency fund built\n- Consistent income\n- Basic insurance covered\n\n**Mid-term (3-5 years):**\n- Investment portfolio started\n- Retirement fund growing\n- Increased rates\n\n**Long-term (10+ years):**\n- Financial independence\n- Passive income streams\n- Comfortable retirement fund\n\n**TOOLS & RESOURCES**\n\n**Apps:**\n- Wallet (expense tracking)\n- Wave (invoicing)\n- Bibit/Ajaib (investing)\n\n**Education:**\n- Financial literacy books\n- Personal finance podcasts\n- Consult financial advisor\n\nFreelancing offers freedom, tapi require financial discipline. Plan well, live well!', 
'/images/articles/freelance-finance.jpg', 
'Bambang Sutrisno', 
'Freelancing', 
NOW(), NOW());

